node.text:
Join us for an unforgettable 5- hour guided experience, that will completely sweep you off your feet! Spend the day interacting with an array of stunning wildlife, catered lunch, jungle music and much more that will transport you to another world! This incredible experience will surely fulfill your bucket list of dreams.
 
ZWF VIP Jungle Experience package includes:
General Wildlife Experience
Animal Presentations
Feline Experience
Primate Experience
Owl Encounter
Catered Lunch (1 hour)
Sloth Encounter
Tamandua Encounter
Watch Limbani paint (No interaction)
Big Cat Photo (Cougar)
#ZWFMiami
#Chimpanzee
#wildlifeadventure 

🎥 @alexis_canovas
@mariowildlife 
@limbanizwf 
@mariazwfmiami
@mattdillon1983

node.text:
We would like to introduce Safia and Nazer to our ZWF Family. These babies were born 7 weeks ago and very weak. We removed them from their mother at only 6 hours of being born due to how delicate their health was.
Nazer was born with severe crooked front paws as well. After weeks of intensive care and therapy he is now walking like a regular lion should.
The mother has been placed on birth control.

node.text:
Congrats to our #QueenOfTheJungle

#Repost @mariazwfmiami
・・・
It’s a Jungle out there but you best believe I have my 👑 on firmly. 😉 

#LinkInBio for the full #coverstory. 

Excited to share my @thecontrastmag cover feature out today. Beyond grateful to the team who put this together and editor @actualmonroe for having me as his cover muse. 

@mattdillon1983 you continually make magic and impress me with your level of work and how much faith and belief you have in me and the brand. 

Many ask me what covers like this do for #ZWFMiami and my response is a brand is multi faceted and building awareness comes in many shapes and forms. I’m proud to use my profile to bring awareness, increase following and bring the @Zwfmiami story to a larger audience globally. 

Finally its my mission to empower women globally and i look forward to sharing my story more in the future to make change. 
_____
From the cover story 👇🏻

Navigating through the world has never been an easy feat. We get so many people telling us who we should be or how we should live our lives, so much so that some people never have a chance to figure out who they really are. Zoological Wildlife Foundation (ZWF) Co-Founder Maria Tabraue not only traverses through a literal jungle with her work, but she also wanders through the jungle of self-identity.
______
Photographer:
Christopher Logan @cloganstudios
Glam: Peggy Mackey @peggymackeybeauty
Styling: Steven Lassalle @stylebylassalle
Producer/PR: Matt Dillon @mattdillon1983
Location: Wuul Studios, Miami, FL. @wuul_studios
Interview: Carlito Locoyo @litoswaay
